@page "/"

<div class="hero-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h1><i class="bi bi-globe rotating-globe"></i> Welcome to World Conquest</h1>
        <p class="lead">Test your geography knowledge and conquer the world, one country at a time!</p>

        <div class="action-buttons">
            <a href="map" class="geo-button primary">
                <i class="bi bi-crosshair"></i>
                Conquer the World
            </a>
            <a href="normal-map" class="geo-button secondary">
                <i class="bi bi-map"></i>
                Learn Geography
            </a>
            <a href="uk-counties" class="geo-button primary">
                <i class="bi bi-flag"></i>
                Conquer UK Administrative Counties
            </a>
                <a href="kent-towns" class="geo-button primary">
                    <i class="bi bi-geo-alt-fill"></i>
                    Conquer Kent Towns & Villages (Not literally)
                </a>
            <a href="shape-game" class='geo-button primary'>
                <i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i>
                Play Country Shape Guessing Game
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <section class="game-instructions">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> How to play</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Objective:</strong> Click countries on the map and identify the country and its capital. The game is
            complete when the
            entire map is green (all countries and capitals have been guessed correctly).
        </p>

        <h3><i class="bi bi-joystick"></i> Map controls</h3>
        <p>The map uses Leaflet for interaction. Use these keyboard and mouse controls to navigate:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pan map</strong>: <kbd>Arrow Keys</kbd> (Left/Right/Up/Down) or click and drag with the left
                mouse
                button.</li>
            <li><strong>Zoom in / out</strong>: Mouse wheel scroll (wheel up = zoom in, wheel down = zoom out), or press
                <kbd>+</kbd> or <kbd>-</kbd> on the keyboard.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Box zoom</strong>: Hold <kbd>Shift</kbd> and drag to draw a rectangle — the map will zoom to fit
                that
                box (Leaflet's box-zoom behavior).</li>
            <li><strong>Continent buttons</strong>: Click a continent button (if visible in the UI) to jump/zoom to that
                continent — this uses the map's continent zoom helper.</li>
            <li><strong>Zoom step keys</strong>: <kbd>=</kbd> usually behaves like <kbd>+</kbd> (useful on keyboards
                where +
                requires Shift).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3><i class="bi bi-palette"></i> Color legend</h3>
        <p>Result colors shown on the map indicate how well a country &amp; its capital were guessed:</p>
        <div class="color-legend">
            <div class="legend-item">
                <div class="legend-color" style="background:#28a745;"></div>
                <div class="legend-text">
                    <strong>Green</strong> — Both the country and its capital were guessed correctly.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="legend-item">
                <div class="legend-color" style="background:#ffc107;"></div>
                <div class="legend-text">
                    <strong>Yellow</strong> — Only the country was guessed correctly.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="legend-item">
                <div class="legend-color" style="background:#007bff;"></div>
                <div class="legend-text">
                    <strong>Blue</strong> — Only the capital was guessed correctly.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>